{"lemma":"فِطْرُ","slug":"فِطْرُ","root":"ف.ط.ر","root_slug":"ف-ط-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ط-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فِطْرُ","root":"فطر","pos":"V","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34131","n34132","n34133","n34134"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rip apart, to rend the seam, to cleave, to break apart, to crack"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split open, to cut open, to slit open, to crack"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lance, to lacerate, to gash, to cut, to make an incision"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to breakfast, to have breakfast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَطَرَ (faṭara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crack, fissure, rift, rupture, cleavage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"breaking of the fast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fungi, mushrooms","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape, to make, to form, to create, to fashion, to compose, to bring forth","examples":[{"text":"فَسَيَقُولُونَ مَنْ يُعِيدُنَا قُلِ الَّذِي فَطَرَكُمْ أَوَّلَ مَرَّةٍ","english":"Then they will say, “Who will bring us back?” Say, “The One Who created you the first time.”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to endow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَطَرَ (faṭara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِطْرَة (fiṭra, “nature, disposition, constitution, temperament, instinct”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate to Hebrew פָטַר (pāṭar, “to set free, to let out, to release, to dismiss”), Aramaic פָטַר (pāṭar, “to cleave, to separate, to free, to discharge”), Aramaic פְטַר (pəṭar, “to free, to release, to dismiss”), Classical Syriac ܦܛܰܪ (pṭar, “to leave, to desist from; to shoot out; to separate, to dissolve; to dismiss”), Ugaritic 𐎔𐎉𐎗 (pṭr, “to split”), hypercorrected Ugaritic 𐎔𐎑𐎗 (pẓr, “to free, to loosen, to let go”), Akkadian 𒃮 (DUḪ /⁠paṭāru⁠/, “to loosen, to detach; to relax, to slacken; to release, to let free; to disperse”), and Ge'ez ፈጠረ (fäṭärä, “to carve; to feign; to create”) which has been borrowed into a second فَطَرَ (faṭara).\n\nFrom Ge'ez ፈጠረ (fäṭärä). Doublet of the former فَطَرَ (faṭara) for the Ethiopic one is cognate."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34131","headword_ar":"فَطْرٌ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see 1: ―         -b2-  as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cleft, split, slit, rent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crack:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a first cleft"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (MF:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTuwrN","text_ar":"فُطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) occurring in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo taraY mino fuTuwrK","text_ar":"هَلْ تَرَى مِنْ فُطُورٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dost thou see any clefts?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the Kur [lxvii. 3]. (TA.)       -A2-  'Omar, being asked respecting [the discharge termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma*oY","text_ar":"المَذْى"},{"kind":"text","text":", answered, It is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaToru","text_ar":"الفَطْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) thus as related by A 'Obeyd: (TA:) it is said that he likened it, in respect of its paucity, to what is drawn from the udder by means of the milking termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaToru","text_ar":"الفَطْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) or, as some say, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafaT~arato qadamaAhu damFA","text_ar":"تَفَطَّرَتْ قَدَمَاهُ دَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above]: (TA:) or he likened its coming forth from the orifice of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akar","text_ar":"ذَكَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the coming forth of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAb","text_ar":"نَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the camel: or, as it is related by En-Nadr, he said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuToru","text_ar":"الفُطْرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm: meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the milk that appears upon the orifice of the teat of the udder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","MF","O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34132","headword_ar":"فُطْرٌ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as has broken forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with buds or leaves] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tafaT~ara","text_ar":"مَا تَفَطَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), of plants. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorN","text_ar":"فِطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  And, (S, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTurN","text_ar":"فُطُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the latter used in poetry, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The toadstool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamoA^ap","text_ar":"كَمْاَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fungus"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white and large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and deadly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [so called] because the ground cleaves asunder from it: (TA:) n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTorapN","text_ar":"فُطْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [Also applied in the present day to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common mushroom; agariens campestris."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any fungus."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  [Also, the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Immaturity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of leaven,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in dough:] see the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTarati","text_ar":"فَطَرَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaroA^apu AlEajiyna","text_ar":"المَرْاَةُ العَجِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTorN","text_ar":"فُطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTurN","text_ar":"فُطُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Somewhat of that which remains of milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the udder"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is then milked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small quantity of milk when it is milked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk at the time when it is milked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n34133","headword_ar":"فِطْرٌ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grapes when the heads thereof appear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) [so called] because the [fruit-] stalks [then] break forth ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanofaTiru","text_ar":"تَنْفَطِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTorN","text_ar":"فُطْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)       -A2-  Also a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoTara","text_ar":"اَفْطَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [as such] it signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking of a fast; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomN","text_ar":"صَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiydu AlfiTori","text_ar":"عِيدُ الفِطْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The festival of the breaking of the fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"immediately after Rama- dán; sometimes called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiToru","text_ar":"الفِطْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiTorapu","text_ar":"الفِطْرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadaqapu AlfiTori","text_ar":"صَدَقَةُ الفِطْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The alms of the breaking of the fast"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O, K, TA,) which is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAE","text_ar":"صَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] of wheat: the prefixed noun ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sdqh","text_ar":"صدقه"},{"kind":"text","text":") is rejected, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is affixed to its complement ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfTr","text_ar":"الفطر"},{"kind":"text","text":") to indicate that such has been done: but it is a word used by the lawyers; not of the classical language. (TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoTirN","text_ar":"مُفْطِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34134","headword_ar":"فُطُرٌ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTorN","text_ar":"فُطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}